  "body": "The yellow paper specifies the gas cost of `ECPAIRING` as 60,000k + 40,000, where `k` is the number of pairs of curve points to check. In reality, it should be 80,000k + 100,000. This is confirmed by cross-referencing with the following implementations:\r\n\r\n[KEVM has](https://github.com/kframework/evm-semantics/blob/ffd9552f3703c0a60b6b3e2262b9430e2764e2f8/evm.md#execution-gas):\r\n```\r\nrule <k> #gasExec(_, ECPAIRING) => 100000 +Int (#sizeWordStack(DATA) /Int 192) *Int 80000 ... </k> <callData> DATA </callData>\r\n```\r\n\r\n[py-evm has](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/814fb0e2d3dccf16225a8c8aadef579f7c9265f6/eth/constants.py#L98)\r\n```\r\nGAS_ECPAIRING_BASE = 100000\r\nGAS_ECPAIRING_PER_POINT = 80000\r\n```\r\n\r\n[aleth has](https://github.com/ethereum/aleth/blob/697f1fb6a606f6c9d55d08f6a91e03ed8676b968/libethcore/Precompiled.cpp#L202)\r\n```\r\nETH_REGISTER_PRECOMPILED_PRICER(alt_bn128_pairing_product)(bytesConstRef _in)\r\n{\r\n\treturn 100000 + (_in.size() / 192) * 80000;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n[parity has](https://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum/blob/master/ethcore/res/ethereum/foundation.json)\r\n```\r\n\t\t\"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000008\": {\r\n\t\t\t\"builtin\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t\"name\": \"alt_bn128_pairing\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\"activate_at\": \"0x42ae50\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\"pricing\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\"alt_bn128_pairing\": {\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"base\": 100000,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"pair\": 80000\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t},\r\n```",
